n = int(input())
    s = list(map(int, input().split()))
    s.sort()
    s = s[::-1]
    max_lucky = 0
    for i in range(len(s)-1):
        if s[i] == s[i+1]:
            continue
        else:
            max_lucky = max_lucky | s[i] | s[i+1]
    print(max_lucky)

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    arr.sort()
    ans = 0
    for i in range(n):
        curr = arr[i]
        j = i - 1
        while j >= 0 and arr[j] + curr <= k:
            j -= 1
        ans = max(ans, i - j)
    print(ans)

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    prices = list(map(int, input().split()))
    prices.sort()
    count = 0
    i = 0
    while k > 0 and i < n:
        if k - prices[i] >= 0:
            count += 1
            k -= prices[i]
        else:
            break
        i += 1
    print(count)
